1
00:00:19,953 --> 00:00:22,114
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

2
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,622
BUG: Now I lay me
down to sleep,

3
00:01:06,699 --> 00:01:08,326
I pray the Lord
my soul to keep.

4
00:01:08,968 --> 00:01:11,198
If I should die
before I wake,

5
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:13,938
I pray the Lord
my soul to take.

6
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:16,100
NEWSCASTER: Before tonight's murder,
there has been no clue

7
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:17,837
as to who
this killer might be.

8
00:01:17,944 --> 00:01:20,572
But now the Riverton Ripper
and the knife he uses

9
00:01:20,647 --> 00:01:23,377
have been caught by a
high-definition security camera.

10
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:24,712
SARAH: Any day, now.
NEWSCASTER: Police say

11
00:01:24,784 --> 00:01:28,015
that the killer is a Caucasian
male in his mid-to-late 30s.

12
00:01:28,088 --> 00:01:29,646
It's too dark to see his face

13
00:01:29,722 --> 00:01:32,885
but the quality of the image has
allowed forensic technicians

14
00:01:32,959 --> 00:01:34,358
to zoom in and
enhance it enough

15
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,054
to make out
the word "Vengeance"

16
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:38,825
etched on the blade
of the Ripper's weapon.

17
00:01:38,898 --> 00:01:40,490
No one was in the
area at the time...

18
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:42,125
SARAH: That's beautiful, Abel.

19
00:01:42,435 --> 00:01:44,596
And Leah's going
to love that house.

20
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,432
Shameless distraction device.

21
00:01:46,806 --> 00:01:47,830
Come to bed.

22
00:01:47,907 --> 00:01:49,738
The news is too scary
for me to watch alone.

23
00:01:49,809 --> 00:01:50,935
Okay, Sarah,
I'll be up soon.

24
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:54,173
NEWSCASTER: We consulted local psychiatrist Dr.
William Blake.

25
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:55,675
Oh, shit!

26
00:01:55,915 --> 00:01:58,042
(GROANING) NEWSCASTER:
Here's what he had to say.

27
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,881
DR.
BLAKE: The identity of a killer of this sort

28
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:02,478
may well not even
be known to himself.

29
00:02:02,555 --> 00:02:04,352
He could be
anywhere and anyone

30
00:02:04,424 --> 00:02:06,756
leading a normal life,
so far as he knows,

31
00:02:06,993 --> 00:02:08,517
and never dream
for an instant that,

32
00:02:08,595 --> 00:02:11,393
every so often,
he turns into a monster.

33
00:02:11,998 --> 00:02:13,056
ABEL: What is this?

34
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,498
NEWSCASTER: Twenty-one-year-old Penny Anderson,

35
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:15,893
a graduate student
at Boston University...

36
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:17,231
WOMAN: (SCREAMING)
Somebody!

37
00:02:17,303 --> 00:02:18,930
NEWSCASTER: ...studying for a Ph.D. in psychology.

38
00:02:19,005 --> 00:02:20,404
WOMAN: Help me!

39
00:02:21,107 --> 00:02:23,166
No!

40
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:24,668
(GASPING)

41
00:02:24,744 --> 00:02:26,735
NEWSCASTER: The victim's
funeral will be held tomorrow at...

42
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:28,474
Dear God, tell me
this is a dream.

43
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:34,716
ABEL (AS JAMES):
What's with the knife, Abel?

44
00:02:34,787 --> 00:02:36,448
What's with the blood?
It's really crazy stuff.

45
00:02:36,589 --> 00:02:39,956
It's not my knife, James!
I don't know what's with it.

46
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,525
(AS PENNY) I think someone has broken in.

47
00:02:41,594 --> 00:02:43,221
(AS BRAD) No one has broken in.
Come on, Penny.

48
00:02:43,296 --> 00:02:44,854
FEMALE VOICE: Please, Abel.
Blake said it could happen.

49
00:02:44,931 --> 00:02:47,126
A one in a million
chance, he said.

50
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,599
(AS PENNY)
What if it did?

51
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:50,863
He said to call him, 24/7.

52
00:02:50,937 --> 00:02:53,098
(AS BRAD) Abel, listen. Call him now.
You've got to call Dr. Blake.

53
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:55,801
(AS PENNY) Please put down the knife.
Call the doctor.

54
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:56,899
FEMALE VOICE:
God will help you.

55
00:02:59,112 --> 00:03:01,603
(AS RIPPER) Call Dr.
Blake, and I kill your family.

56
00:03:01,714 --> 00:03:03,511
(GASPING)

57
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:06,381
Sorry, sorry,
I just need a hug.

58
00:03:06,619 --> 00:03:09,110
That knife is so scary,
you know?

59
00:03:09,622 --> 00:03:10,646
What knife?

60
00:03:10,723 --> 00:03:13,317
SARAH: The Ripper's.
They've got it on tape.

61
00:03:13,993 --> 00:03:16,325
RIPPER: Don't do something stupid, Abel.

62
00:03:16,462 --> 00:03:17,451
Here's the deal.

63
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:20,988
Just look the other way when I
kill and your family stays alive.

64
00:03:22,402 --> 00:03:26,099
Turn me in,
and you'll live alone in a house of blood.

65
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:27,864
(GASPS)

66
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:29,499
(PHONE RINGING)

67
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,338
Hello?

68
00:03:33,413 --> 00:03:35,278
Abel, this is Dr. Blake.
Is everything okay?

69
00:03:35,348 --> 00:03:37,839
No, no, no. Everything is not okay.
I found something.

70
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:40,050
What did you find?

71
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,346
A knife.

72
00:03:41,421 --> 00:03:44,857
Under my bench.
And not just any knife.

73
00:03:44,924 --> 00:03:46,824
The one on TV.
The Ripper's knife.

74
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,054
I swear before God,
Dr. Blake, I didn't know.

75
00:03:49,128 --> 00:03:50,891
But the second that I went to
call you there was somebody,

76
00:03:50,997 --> 00:03:53,591
and he said
don't call you, or else...

77
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:55,634
DR. BLAKE: Or else?

78
00:03:55,702 --> 00:03:56,999
What?

79
00:03:57,070 --> 00:04:00,631
Or else he would
kill Sarah. And Leah.

80
00:04:00,707 --> 00:04:01,833
And the others, too.

81
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:05,139
Abel, I'll be there in 10 minutes.
I want you to tell Sarah

82
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:08,039
to take Leah,
and drive to her sister's.

83
00:04:08,114 --> 00:04:10,378
I haven't told her
about this part of my life.

84
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,940
But you swore
to me you would.

85
00:04:12,018 --> 00:04:13,007
That's part
of the agreement.

86
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,644
Just get here
before it's too late!

87
00:04:14,721 --> 00:04:18,851
DR. BLAKE: Abel,
have Sarah drive to May's house, with Leah.

88
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,256
May is working nights
and Sarah is sound asleep.

89
00:04:21,327 --> 00:04:22,624
I can't just wake her up.

90
00:04:22,695 --> 00:04:24,219
DR. BLAKE: You have to!

91
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:26,162
Abel?

92
00:04:26,232 --> 00:04:27,927
You there?

93
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:29,593
Abel?

94
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:37,806
(SCREAMING)

95
00:04:39,379 --> 00:04:41,210
ABEL: No! No!

96
00:04:46,986 --> 00:04:49,113
DR. BLAKE: What the hell are you looking at?
Break the door down.

97
00:04:49,188 --> 00:04:50,485
ABEL: I won't let
you do this! I won't!

98
00:04:50,556 --> 00:04:51,750
DR. BLAKE:
Open the door. Abel!

99
00:04:51,824 --> 00:04:52,916
ABEL: I won't...

100
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,760
DR. BLAKE: Abel!

101
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:57,222
PATERSON: Police, open up!

102
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:58,662
BOBBY: Mr. Plenkov, open up.

103
00:04:58,731 --> 00:04:59,993
DR. BLAKE: Abel,
open the door!

104
00:05:00,066 --> 00:05:01,658
BOBBY: Plenkov! Open up!

105
00:05:01,734 --> 00:05:03,133
PATERSON: Kick it in, Bobby.

106
00:05:03,903 --> 00:05:05,063
(DOOR CRASHING OPEN)

107
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:07,129
DR. BLAKE: Get up
those stairs now!

108
00:05:07,573 --> 00:05:09,666
PATERSON: Which room?
On the right?

109
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:12,338
Mr. Plenkov! Mr. Plenkov!

110
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:13,640
(GROWLING)
Freeze!

111
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:14,873
(GUNSHOTS)

112
00:05:14,947 --> 00:05:16,107
Shit!

113
00:05:16,683 --> 00:05:18,173
Bobby, check him!
Check him!

114
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:19,581
Hey, sweetie.
Hey, sweetie, come here.

115
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:20,880
Come here.
What's your name?

116
00:05:20,953 --> 00:05:22,215
BOBBY: No pulse, Frank.
What's your name, huh?

117
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:24,153
BOBBY: I'll check the woman.
No, no, no, no, look at me.

118
00:05:24,223 --> 00:05:26,384
You're okay, all right?
You're okay.

119
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:28,984
Get away from me.

120
00:05:30,863 --> 00:05:32,296
Bobby.
Yeah?

121
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:33,593
Get her downstairs.

122
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:35,861
BOBBY: Hey, sweetheart,
here we go.

123
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:40,065
I got you.
You're going to be fine.

124
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:41,766
PATERSON: Get in here.
Cover us.

125
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,035
PATERSON: He's dead.

126
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:44,770
So is Elvis.
You never know.

127
00:05:45,111 --> 00:05:46,135
You have an epi?

128
00:05:46,212 --> 00:05:47,577
We got it.

129
00:05:47,914 --> 00:05:50,314
JEANNE: The mother is dead, too.
Way dead.

130
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:53,244
You missed the kid,
you fuck.

131
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:55,048
(AS RIPPER)
I'll get them all next time.

132
00:05:55,822 --> 00:05:57,414
Son of a bitch!

133
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:01,190
GUS: Epinephrine kicks ass!

134
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:02,989
Hey! Hey!

135
00:06:03,896 --> 00:06:05,989
JEANNE: Let's get
the gurney, Gus.

136
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:10,035
Abel, I'll get you
to a hospital. Abel?

137
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:12,064
You piece of shit.

138
00:06:12,572 --> 00:06:13,664
He's not a monster.

139
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:15,901
What do you
call him, then?

140
00:06:16,008 --> 00:06:17,737
I call him mentally ill.

141
00:06:19,078 --> 00:06:21,137
(AS ABEL) Thank you
for stopping me.

142
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:22,940
Abel.

143
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:24,843
Forgive me.

144
00:06:25,485 --> 00:06:26,816
He's talking to you.

145
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,719
Please!

146
00:06:29,322 --> 00:06:31,256
Would it hurt you
to be human?

147
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:32,856
Just once?

148
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:37,392
We'll let
God sort it out.

149
00:06:37,463 --> 00:06:38,828
Thank you.

150
00:06:41,968 --> 00:06:43,162
(SCREAMING)

151
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,498
No, Abel!

152
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,470
Abel, talk to me.

153
00:06:46,539 --> 00:06:48,131
(AS RIPPER)
Abel's not here.

154
00:06:52,011 --> 00:06:53,842
This is for you, you cunt!

155
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:55,505
(GUNSHOT)

156
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:57,880
That's for shut the fuck up.

157
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:08,018
How's Mrs. King doing?

158
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,254
Baby is two months premature.

159
00:07:09,328 --> 00:07:11,023
Dr. Carrie says
he's blind, too.

160
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,997
Seven births in one hour,
all premature.

161
00:07:13,065 --> 00:07:14,327
What's going on here?
Anarchy!

162
00:07:15,067 --> 00:07:16,056
MAY: What else you got?

163
00:07:16,135 --> 00:07:19,070
We got a cop, Frank Paterson,
who took two in the vest.

164
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:20,935
And?
And we got a perp.

165
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:22,474
Go on.
Mid-30s,

166
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:25,943
white male,
under constraint and critical.

167
00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:29,641
Took multiple gunshots and stab wounds.
EEG flat.

168
00:07:29,715 --> 00:07:32,445
Oh, and are you ready for this?
We think he's the Ripper.

169
00:07:32,518 --> 00:07:33,951
What?
Family guy.

170
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,385
Killed the wife,
tried to kill his kid.

171
00:07:35,755 --> 00:07:36,779
You got a name?

172
00:07:37,056 --> 00:07:38,956
Plenkov. Abel Plenkov.

173
00:07:41,561 --> 00:07:42,755
GUS: May, you copy?

174
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:45,090
May?

175
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,792
He said he'd get
them all next time.

176
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:49,528
What do you think
he meant?

177
00:07:49,769 --> 00:07:51,862
Maybe he was talking about his other personalities.

178
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:54,467
My family is from Haiti.

179
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,802
And down there they don't say

180
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:58,343
that someone like him
has multiple personalities.

181
00:07:58,411 --> 00:07:59,844
What do they say he has?

182
00:08:00,413 --> 00:08:01,937
Multiple souls.

183
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:03,540
What's the difference?

184
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:06,816
Personalities die
when the patient dies.

185
00:08:06,886 --> 00:08:07,978
Souls live on.

186
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:13,019
It's all just superstition,
I suppose.

187
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:17,589
Could you hand me
my jacket, please?

188
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:20,023
It's cold as hell in here.

189
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:23,692
Thanks.

190
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:27,097
Is this your evidence bag?

191
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,964
(SCREAMING)

192
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:32,841
Get that fucker
under control!

193
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:36,738
(RIPPER LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

194
00:08:36,983 --> 00:08:37,972
(SCREAMING)

195
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:45,122
Shit!

196
00:08:50,329 --> 00:08:51,421
Frank!

197
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:52,896
I can't believe
you fucking guys!

198
00:08:52,965 --> 00:08:54,330
You're supposed
to be watching him!

199
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,027
You all right?
You good? Fuck you!

200
00:08:56,102 --> 00:08:57,933
You're all right. GUS: Let me see.
Get out of my way.

201
00:08:58,004 --> 00:08:59,631
Where the hell is Plenkov?
GUS: Let me see!

202
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,199
PATERSON: Shit. Fix that!

203
00:09:05,511 --> 00:09:07,843
PATERSON: Call for backup!
I got Plenkov!

204
00:09:14,687 --> 00:09:15,881
PATERSON: Fuck!

205
00:09:30,503 --> 00:09:35,338
CROWD: One, two,
three, four, five,

206
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:40,505
six, seven, eight,
nine, ten,

207
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:43,014
11, 12!

208
00:09:45,551 --> 00:09:47,985
BRANDON: The lights out!

209
00:09:48,054 --> 00:09:49,578
(ALARM RINGING)
(GASPING)

210
00:09:49,655 --> 00:09:51,247
BRANDON: Midnight!

211
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:53,252
All right! This is it!

212
00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:55,055
Let the day begin!

213
00:09:55,127 --> 00:09:57,789
(ALL CHEERING)

214
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:04,695
As you all know,

215
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:06,928
Ripper Day
marks two things.

216
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:09,201
One of them bad,
one of them good.

217
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:13,507
The good part is,
it's the birthday of seven of us here

218
00:10:13,579 --> 00:10:16,309
born 16 years ago tonight.

219
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:18,576
Jerome King.

220
00:10:18,651 --> 00:10:20,175
Hey, Jerome.
(ALL WHOOPING)

221
00:10:20,753 --> 00:10:22,345
Alex Dunkelman.

222
00:10:23,856 --> 00:10:26,222
Jay Chan, with a new
Ripper puppet tonight.

223
00:10:26,926 --> 00:10:28,086
Bug Hellerman...

224
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:30,853
Hellerman?

225
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:32,724
ALEX: It's about time!

226
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:35,130
BRANDON: Better late than never,
I suppose.

227
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:37,328
Where you been?
Sleeping.

228
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:39,132
It's okay, Bug
takes a little longer

229
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:40,797
because he's a little
slower, I guess.

230
00:10:40,873 --> 00:10:41,897
(ALL LAUGHING)

231
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:44,772
Moving on to Penelope Bryte over there,
by the ambulance,

232
00:10:44,844 --> 00:10:48,405
who, incidentally, knows God.
They speak daily.

233
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:52,178
And to the beautiful and
gorgeous Brittany Cunningham.

234
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:55,245
And last, but,
of course, not least...

235
00:10:55,521 --> 00:10:56,988
ALL: Brandon O'Neil!

236
00:10:57,056 --> 00:10:58,284
Yes, sir!

237
00:10:58,357 --> 00:10:59,722
(ALL CHEERING)

238
00:10:59,792 --> 00:11:02,625
Thank you, thank you,
thank you very much. Pleasure.

239
00:11:03,029 --> 00:11:06,226
Now, it's time for
the bad part, people.

240
00:11:06,699 --> 00:11:08,667
We of the Riverton Seven

241
00:11:08,734 --> 00:11:12,295
have had to share our birthday
with a monster,

242
00:11:12,805 --> 00:11:15,069
the serial killer
Abel Plenkov,

243
00:11:15,141 --> 00:11:17,268
who died at midnight
the day we were born.

244
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:20,469
It's the Ripper.
CROWD: Ooh.

245
00:11:20,546 --> 00:11:23,242
Legend has it that we,
the Riverton Seven,

246
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:26,341
are the mirrors of Abel Plenkov's personalities.

247
00:11:26,419 --> 00:11:28,250
The ones that
turned the Ripper in.

248
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,652
And that the Ripper
still wants revenge.

249
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:32,691
So Abel Plenkov is dead,

250
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:35,486
but his ghost isn't.

251
00:11:35,795 --> 00:11:39,754
No, it lurks underneath the old railroad bridge.
