01:15:57,719 --> 01:15:58,879
What's that?

1518
01:16:00,489 --> 01:16:02,753
The biggest knife
I could find in the kitchen.

1519
01:16:03,292 --> 01:16:04,316
Bug...

1520
01:16:05,794 --> 01:16:07,523
What would you say

1521
01:16:08,163 --> 01:16:10,256
if I told you I was
going to kill you, Alex?

1522
01:16:12,000 --> 01:16:13,228
I'd say you weren't.

1523
01:16:13,669 --> 01:16:14,727
Why not?

1524
01:16:14,803 --> 01:16:16,395
Because you're
my best friend.

1525
01:16:18,106 --> 01:16:19,505
You're Bug.

1526
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:26,406
Now you ask me.

1527
01:16:34,022 --> 01:16:35,990
You don't think
I could kill somebody?

1528
01:16:36,058 --> 01:16:37,116
No.

1529
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:40,157
You'd be wrong, Bug.

1530
01:16:41,430 --> 01:16:42,488
Dead wrong.

1531
01:16:43,298 --> 01:16:45,163
You killed Penelope
and Jay?

1532
01:16:45,367 --> 01:16:46,425
And the others?

1533
01:16:46,568 --> 01:16:47,830
(ALEX GRUNTING)

1534
01:16:49,438 --> 01:16:50,962
Of course not.

1535
01:16:53,976 --> 01:16:55,944
I killed my stepfather.

1536
01:16:58,814 --> 01:16:59,838
You killed Quint?

1537
01:17:00,282 --> 01:17:02,273
He was drunk.

1538
01:17:02,351 --> 01:17:03,716
He hit me.

1539
01:17:04,753 --> 01:17:07,551
For the first time in my life,
I hit him back.

1540
01:17:07,623 --> 01:17:10,091
Fell down the steps
and broke his stupid neck.

1541
01:17:10,258 --> 01:17:12,920
Alex, it's okay, okay?

1542
01:17:13,095 --> 01:17:14,392
No, it's not okay!

1543
01:17:14,696 --> 01:17:16,789
What I did...
It's not okay for everybody

1544
01:17:16,865 --> 01:17:18,696
to be killing each
other all the time!

1545
01:17:27,476 --> 01:17:28,875
You don't want
something to drink?

1546
01:17:30,946 --> 01:17:32,208
You got rat poison?

1547
01:17:33,882 --> 01:17:36,373
No, we just ran
out of rat poison.

1548
01:17:37,219 --> 01:17:39,119
I'm going to go get you water.

1549
01:17:56,805 --> 01:17:58,966
(SIGHS)

1550
01:18:25,667 --> 01:18:27,134
What is this?

1551
01:18:50,992 --> 01:18:52,516
(CLATTERING)

1552
01:19:24,793 --> 01:19:25,885
Alex, I'll be right...

1553
01:20:08,837 --> 01:20:09,929
Ripper?

1554
01:20:10,005 --> 01:20:11,336
(SCREAMING)
Son of a bitch!

1555
01:20:16,411 --> 01:20:18,208
Drop the knife, Bug.

1556
01:20:18,647 --> 01:20:19,739
Now.

1557
01:20:21,650 --> 01:20:23,277
Kick it over to me.

1558
01:20:29,524 --> 01:20:31,515
I'm sorry, I thought
you were somebody else.

1559
01:20:31,693 --> 01:20:33,251
Get your hands up.

1560
01:20:33,328 --> 01:20:34,556
Up.

1561
01:20:34,629 --> 01:20:35,721
Walk slow.

1562
01:20:40,902 --> 01:20:42,164
Why are you
pointing that at me?

1563
01:20:42,237 --> 01:20:44,330
That is far enough.

1564
01:20:45,073 --> 01:20:46,165
Why?

1565
01:20:47,142 --> 01:20:49,076
Your phone was found next to
Brittany Cunningham's body.

1566
01:20:49,144 --> 01:20:50,577
It fell into her
purse at school.

1567
01:20:50,645 --> 01:20:52,408
That was an accident.
You can ask my mom.

1568
01:20:52,547 --> 01:20:55,175
Your mom is why
I have to arrest you, Bug.

1569
01:21:00,922 --> 01:21:01,980
Mom!

1570
01:21:02,290 --> 01:21:03,814
Easy!

1571
01:21:06,027 --> 01:21:08,154
Stay there.

1572
01:21:13,835 --> 01:21:15,063
I was there

1573
01:21:15,270 --> 01:21:18,171
when they cut you out
of your mother, Bug.

1574
01:21:19,875 --> 01:21:23,504
You were the one thing that made
the whole bloody mess bearable.

1575
01:21:23,678 --> 01:21:25,043
A fucking...
Miracle?

1576
01:21:25,113 --> 01:21:26,239
Yes!

1577
01:21:27,115 --> 01:21:28,878
Something bright in the dark.

1578
01:21:29,050 --> 01:21:30,449
And ever since,

1579
01:21:30,518 --> 01:21:33,510
for all of us that were there, Bug,
that's what you've been.

1580
01:21:34,556 --> 01:21:37,024
Fuck. How could you do this?

1581
01:21:38,894 --> 01:21:40,225
I didn't.

1582
01:21:42,130 --> 01:21:44,155
Hold out your hands, son.

1583
01:21:46,401 --> 01:21:47,868
Where's my sister?

1584
01:21:47,936 --> 01:21:49,665
Why don't you tell me?

1585
01:21:54,209 --> 01:21:55,767
(SCREAMING)

1586
01:21:59,347 --> 01:22:00,712
RIPPER: It's time.

1587
01:22:53,068 --> 01:22:54,433
(RIPPER YELLING)

1588
01:22:54,502 --> 01:22:55,935
(RIPPER LAUGHING)

1589
01:23:00,275 --> 01:23:03,642
RIPPER: (SOFTLY) They never should've
cut you out of your dead mother.

1590
01:23:21,429 --> 01:23:23,021
(DOOR SQUEAKING)

1591
01:23:48,123 --> 01:23:49,954
(RIPPER SNARLING)

1592
01:23:56,698 --> 01:23:58,325
(GUN FIRES)

1593
01:23:59,401 --> 01:24:01,164
(RIPPER LAUGHS)

1594
01:24:01,236 --> 01:24:03,761
RIPPER: What happened
to your wings, angel?

1595
01:24:05,840 --> 01:24:07,000
(RIPPER EXCLAIMING)

1596
01:24:07,075 --> 01:24:08,906
(GUNSHOTS)

1597
01:24:14,215 --> 01:24:15,842
RIPPER: Fucking piece of shit!

1598
01:24:21,489 --> 01:24:22,547
Where is the knife?

1599
01:24:24,893 --> 01:24:26,986
(SHUSHING) Shut the fuck up.
Shut up.

1600
01:24:36,704 --> 01:24:39,901
RIPPER: Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

1601
01:24:42,811 --> 01:24:44,278
(DOOR OPENING)

1602
01:24:45,880 --> 01:24:47,313
Eww.

1603
01:24:47,382 --> 01:24:49,179
It's not as bad
as it looks.

1604
01:24:49,250 --> 01:24:50,808
How did you get away?

1605
01:24:50,885 --> 01:24:52,750
I was already in the car.

1606
01:24:52,821 --> 01:24:57,417
I came inside just to see where May was,
and I found her dead.

1607
01:24:58,860 --> 01:25:01,158
I knew that fucker
would come for us.

1608
01:25:05,100 --> 01:25:07,625
Maybe he's gone.

1609
01:25:07,802 --> 01:25:09,429
No, no, no.
Let's go.

1610
01:25:09,971 --> 01:25:11,063
(SHUSHING)

1611
01:25:11,139 --> 01:25:12,231
I think we should...

1612
01:25:12,307 --> 01:25:13,569
(RIPPER YELLING)

1613
01:25:15,210 --> 01:25:16,734
(BUG YELLING)

1614
01:25:20,982 --> 01:25:24,076
Die! Die! Die!

1615
01:25:31,993 --> 01:25:33,858
I saved you
for last!

1616
01:25:33,928 --> 01:25:35,589
(CRASHING)

1617
01:25:37,098 --> 01:25:38,258
Fuck!

1618
01:25:43,905 --> 01:25:45,133
Leah, call the cops.

1619
01:25:47,909 --> 01:25:49,501
FANG: Son of a bitch!

1620
01:25:51,479 --> 01:25:54,073
Hey.
Leah, I need you to get the lights on.

1621
01:25:54,149 --> 01:25:56,174
Get out of the house,
get to the neighbors and call the cops.

1622
01:25:56,251 --> 01:25:57,377
You think you
can do that for me?

1623
01:25:57,452 --> 01:25:58,885
What are you going to do?

1624
01:25:58,953 --> 01:26:00,477
I'm going to give
that fucker a 10.

1625
01:26:00,555 --> 01:26:02,216
Make it a 20.

1626
01:26:10,498 --> 01:26:12,159
(PANTING)

1627
01:26:33,087 --> 01:26:34,349
(RATTLING)

1628
01:26:37,225 --> 01:26:38,453
BUG: Ripper?

1629
01:26:38,526 --> 01:26:39,925
(DOOR OPENING)

1630
01:26:41,129 --> 01:26:42,289
Shit!

1631
01:26:42,363 --> 01:26:43,625
(DOOR CLOSING)

1632
01:27:27,875 --> 01:27:29,809
(EXCLAIMING)

1633
01:27:29,877 --> 01:27:32,243
Jerome! Jerome,
stop it! Jerome!

1634
01:27:32,313 --> 01:27:33,712
Hey, hey! Hey!

1635
01:27:35,550 --> 01:27:36,642
Hey.

1636
01:27:41,456 --> 01:27:42,684
Jerome.

1637
01:27:43,124 --> 01:27:44,216
Jerome.

1638
01:27:44,292 --> 01:27:45,452
The Ripper's up here, Bug.

1639
01:27:45,526 --> 01:27:46,550
Watch out.

1640
01:27:46,628 --> 01:27:47,822
It's okay, Jerome.
He's gone, all right?

1641
01:27:47,895 --> 01:27:49,760
What are you doing here?
You're supposed to be at the church.

1642
01:27:49,831 --> 01:27:53,562
Alex called me.
He said all three of us should be together.

1643
01:27:53,801 --> 01:27:55,826
Watch each other's backs.

1644
01:27:56,204 --> 01:27:57,432
I was halfway
through the window

1645
01:27:57,505 --> 01:27:59,837
when the Ripper stabbed me.

1646
01:27:59,907 --> 01:28:00,896
How did he get up here?

1647
01:28:00,975 --> 01:28:03,910
He must have come up
the rope like I did.

1648
01:28:03,978 --> 01:28:07,641
I passed out on the roof,
and then I came to

1649
01:28:07,815 --> 01:28:10,579
and I heard fighting.
Was that you?

1650
01:28:11,886 --> 01:28:14,616
Him and me. Yeah, it was.
He was kicking my ass, too.

1651
01:28:14,689 --> 01:28:18,090
I tried calling the cops
but I knocked over something,

1652
01:28:18,159 --> 01:28:19,649
and then I heard him
coming for me,

1653
01:28:19,727 --> 01:28:21,354
so I ducked
for the closet.

1654
01:28:21,729 --> 01:28:23,219
You saved my life, Jerome.

1655
01:28:23,298 --> 01:28:24,595
I did?

1656
01:28:24,666 --> 01:28:26,964
Yeah, he was going to kill me,
and then you distracted him.

1657
01:28:27,168 --> 01:28:28,328
Good.

1658
01:28:28,403 --> 01:28:30,564
Dude, it's going to be okay.
Help is coming, all right?

1659
01:28:30,638 --> 01:28:32,765
You fought the Ripper, Bug.

1660
01:28:34,208 --> 01:28:37,234
You're a hero,
like I told you.

1661
01:28:37,312 --> 01:28:39,075
(BREATHING SHALLOWLY)

1662
01:28:41,215 --> 01:28:43,706
I'm not a hero,
Jerome. I'm just...

1663
01:28:47,455 --> 01:28:48,513
Jerome?

1664
01:28:49,190 --> 01:28:50,384
Jerome?

1665
01:29:16,784 --> 01:29:18,342
(CLATTERING)

1666
01:29:19,887 --> 01:29:21,377
What the fuck
happened to you?

1667
01:29:23,891 --> 01:29:24,915
What happened to Jerome?

1668
01:29:28,963 --> 01:29:30,089
He's dead.

1669
01:29:30,331 --> 01:29:32,094
The Ripper got him.

1670
01:29:33,167 --> 01:29:34,600
A lot's happened since
you've been gone, Alex.

1671
01:29:34,669 --> 01:29:35,795
Where did you disappear to?

1672
01:29:35,970 --> 01:29:37,904
I saw Paterson
pulling up outside.

1673
01:29:37,972 --> 01:29:39,405
I ran. I hid in the woods.

1674
01:29:39,474 --> 01:29:40,907
Then I heard gunshots,
so I came back.

1675
01:29:40,975 --> 01:29:42,966
I was afraid he shot
you or something.

1676
01:29:43,077 --> 01:29:44,305
Where is he, anyway?

1677
01:29:44,379 --> 01:29:45,607
Downstairs. He's dead.

1678
01:29:45,713 --> 01:29:46,737
What?

1679
01:29:46,814 --> 01:29:48,372
What happened?
The Ripper happened.

1680
01:29:49,751 --> 01:29:51,241
He killed Mom, too.

1681
01:29:51,419 --> 01:29:52,943
(EXHALING)

1682
01:29:53,454 --> 01:29:54,580
May?

1683
01:29:56,724 --> 01:29:58,248
I can't believe this.

1684
01:29:58,493 --> 01:30:00,154
You went to get me
a glass of water

1685
01:30:00,228 --> 01:30:02,924
and now your mom, Paterson,
and Jerome are dead?

1686
01:30:05,533 --> 01:30:06,625
Where were you?

1687
01:30:07,201 --> 01:30:08,668
I ran into Penelope.

1688
01:30:09,103 --> 01:30:10,764
Penelope is dead, Bug.

1689
01:30:12,340 --> 01:30:14,774
I saw her in the
bathroom mirror.

1690
01:30:14,942 --> 01:30:18,400
She brought me Ripper's knife,
and she made me take it.

1691
01:30:26,387 --> 01:30:27,445
Then I heard
something downstairs

1692
01:30:27,522 --> 01:30:30,787
and I went to come check on you,
and you were gone.

1693
01:30:32,760 --> 01:30:35,661
Paterson wasn't after you.
He was after me.

1694
01:30:36,631 --> 01:30:39,566
He thought that I killed Brittany and my Mom.

1695
01:30:41,102 --> 01:30:42,535
It was the Ripper.

1696
01:30:42,703 --> 01:30:44,500
And where is the Ripper now?

1697
01:30:45,206 --> 01:30:47,265
I guess he got away
out my window.

1698
01:30:47,341 --> 01:30:49,866
Or went out Leah's.
Hers is open, too.

1699
01:30:50,511 --> 01:30:52,445
And he tried to stab me
to death with his...

1700
01:30:52,613 --> 01:30:53,637
Stab you with what?

1701
01:30:53,881 --> 01:30:56,111
With his knife.
I thought you had his knife.

1702
01:30:56,818 --> 01:30:57,876
I did, but...

1703
01:30:58,186 --> 01:30:59,847
Did you kill them, Bug?

1704
01:31:00,288 --> 01:31:01,380
What?

1705
01:31:01,556 --> 01:31:02,614
No, l...

1706
01:31:03,057 --> 01:31:04,649
I didn't kill anybody.

1707
01:31:05,059 --> 01:31:06,959
Not that you remember.

1708
01:31:09,697 --> 01:31:11,722
Bug, I got to tell
you something.

1709
01:31:11,899 --> 01:31:13,491
And don't get upset.

1710
01:31:13,568 --> 01:31:14,694
What?

1711
01:31:14,902 --> 01:31:16,995
My mom told me this.

1712
01:31:17,171 --> 01:31:18,263
Your father

1713
01:31:18,339 --> 01:31:21,775
was first diagnosed with
schizophrenia when he was 16.

1714
01:31:22,009 --> 01:31:23,135
Just like you are now.

1715
01:31:23,211 --> 01:31:24,473
What are you saying?

1716
01:31:24,545 --> 01:31:27,844
It's hereditary.
Plus, you were in your dead Mom forever.

1717
01:31:27,915 --> 01:31:29,746
Oxygen deprivation.

1718
01:31:29,817 --> 01:31:31,648
It can make you crazy, too.

1719
01:31:31,853 --> 01:31:33,718
Maybe all this stuff
you've been describing

1720
01:31:33,788 --> 01:31:36,655
didn't happen exactly
the way you're saying it did.

1721
01:31:37,225 --> 01:31:38,351
You think I'm crazy?

1722
01:31:38,426 --> 01:31:40,189
No, I don't know
what I think.

1723
01:31:40,261 --> 01:31:42,491
But I'm not walking away.
I've stuck by you through everything.

1724
01:31:42,563 --> 01:31:44,531
Through nightmares and migraines, hell,
puking vultures

1725
01:31:44,599 --> 01:31:46,794
when everybody else was
calling you a ticking time bomb.

1726
01:31:46,868 --> 01:31:49,962
So, if you're not innocent anymore,
that's okay.

1727
01:31:50,872 --> 01:31:53,966
I mean, I killed my stepfather tonight.
I'm no angel, either.

1728
01:31:54,075 --> 01:31:55,838
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

1729
01:32:02,450 --> 01:32:04,782
I'm not innocent
anymore, Alex.

1730
01:32:06,220 --> 01:32:08,848
Not with all of them
inside me now.

1731
01:32:08,923 --> 01:32:10,322
What?

1732
01:32:12,393 --> 01:32:13,724
With who inside you?

1733
01:32:13,895 --> 01:32:15,920
The rest of the
Riverton Seven.

1734
01:32:16,297 --> 01:32:17,321
Even Jerome.

1735
01:32:18,165 --> 01:32:20,565
All their souls
are with me now.

1736
01:32:24,472 --> 01:32:27,737
Bug, maybe you should sit down
and take a few deep breaths.

1737
01:32:27,808 --> 01:32:29,070
You think I'm crazy?

1738
01:32:29,243 --> 01:32:31,677
I'm actually a lot smarter
than I was yesterday.

1739
01:32:31,846 --> 01:32:33,939
Let me ask you a question.

1740
01:32:37,785 --> 01:32:39,343
Why is there blood
on your left ear?

1741
01:32:39,420 --> 01:32:40,682
What?

1742
01:32:41,088 --> 01:32:42,146
The top.

1743
01:32:43,057 --> 01:32:44,081
(EXCLAIMING)

1744
01:32:44,158 --> 01:32:45,250
Hey!

1745
01:32:47,461 --> 01:32:49,622
Almost like you were hit
with a vase or something.

1746
01:32:50,298 --> 01:32:51,492
Brandon told me
to look for that.

1747
01:32:51,566 --> 01:32:53,864
Bug, you are
officially bat-shit nuts.

1748
01:32:53,935 --> 01:32:55,630
I scraped it
climbing up the roof.

1749
01:32:55,703 --> 01:32:57,534
Come on,
let's get real, here.

1750
01:32:57,805 --> 01:33:00,365
BUG: Jay says that Ripper's
getup was a costume for sure.

1751
01:33:01,142 --> 01:33:02,700
Oh, and Brittany
has run a timeline.

1752
01:33:03,144 --> 01:33:04,941
You would've had
enough time to kill Mom

1753
01:33:05,012 --> 01:33:06,673
and put the knife
in the bathroom sink

1754
01:33:06,747 --> 01:33:09,113
while I was hiding under the bed
and Leah was outside in the car.

1755
01:33:09,850 --> 01:33:10,839
And if Jerome came
through the window

1756
01:33:10,918 --> 01:33:12,977
when I was in the bathroom
getting you water,

1757
01:33:13,054 --> 01:33:16,490
you would've had time to stab him,
and go downstairs and kill Paterson.

1758
01:33:16,991 --> 01:33:19,585
You might have
tried to kill me, too.

1759
01:33:19,660 --> 01:33:21,560
Fuck.
BUG: But if you'd heard Jerome upstairs,

1760
01:33:21,629 --> 01:33:25,360
you would've had to get up
there before he called the cops.

1761
01:33:27,368 --> 01:33:30,269
I could've killed you
off earlier, remember?

1762
01:33:30,338 --> 01:33:34,502
Bug, you've watched one too
many Law and Order reruns.

1763
01:33:34,575 --> 01:33:36,236
Besides,
I'm a little guy.

1764
01:33:36,711 --> 01:33:39,077
You could beat me up
in, like, 10 seconds.

1765
01:33:39,246 --> 01:33:40,975
Unless you had
the bad soul in you.

1766
01:33:41,882 --> 01:33:43,873
And then you would fight
like you were possessed.

1767
01:33:44,318 --> 01:33:45,979
Can't fucking believe you.

1768
01:33:47,488 --> 01:33:49,649
You're Adam Plenkov!

1769
01:33:50,358 --> 01:33:52,349
The son of a mass murderer!

1770
01:33:52,426 --> 01:33:53,723
Everybody in your house,

1771
01:33:53,794 --> 01:33:56,763
and all your friends, except me,
have been murdered.

1772
01:33:56,831 --> 01:33:59,026
If there's a bad soul
here, you have it.

1773
01:33:59,100 --> 01:34:00,965
And you got it
from your father.

1774
01:34:01,268 --> 01:34:02,963
Maybe you have
been in institutions.

1775
01:34:03,037 --> 01:34:05,972
Maybe you have killed people,
just in your last life.

1776
01:34:06,140 --> 01:34:08,700
But you're too stupid
and blind to see that.

1777
01:34:10,911 --> 01:34:12,469
Maybe they'll find
your Ripper costume

1778
01:34:12,546 --> 01:34:15,379
buried along with
your stupid condor outfit.

1779
01:34:15,449 --> 01:34:17,747
And they will come
for you with torches.

1780
01:34:19,053 --> 01:34:20,213
What?

1781
01:34:21,088 --> 01:34:23,750
I didn't bury any Ripper costume with my condor.

1782
01:34:24,992 --> 01:34:26,482
(AS RIPPER)
Somebody did.

1783
01:34:28,295 --> 01:34:29,592
(EXHALING)

1784
01:34:31,565 --> 01:34:33,055
You son of a...

1785
01:34:35,870 --> 01:34:38,532
Evil doesn't forget
betrayal, Plenkov.

1786
01:34:38,606 --> 01:34:40,506
You and the other
sick Dr. Blake got me

1787
01:34:40,574 --> 01:34:42,132
and then ran away
like cowards.

1788
01:34:42,209 --> 01:34:44,268
Jumped into the first babies
you could hide in.

1789
01:34:44,345 --> 01:34:45,972
So I saved you for last.

1790
01:34:46,213 --> 01:34:47,305
And I'll kill you now,

1791
01:34:47,381 --> 01:34:48,905
or you can say
yes to a deal.

1792
01:34:48,983 --> 01:34:50,177
What deal?

1793
01:34:50,451 --> 01:34:53,147
Same one I offered your father,
16 years ago today.

1794
01:34:53,254 --> 01:34:56,485
Say yes, and you live. Say no,
and I'll cut your throat.

1795
01:34:56,791 --> 01:34:58,452
Say yes to what?

1796
01:34:58,526 --> 01:35:00,858
To my happy ending
of Riverton's fairytale.

1797
01:35:00,995 --> 01:35:02,155
There was no Ripper.

1798
01:35:02,229 --> 01:35:03,628
Just one of the
Riverton Seven

1799
01:35:03,764 --> 01:35:06,130
that was a little crazy,
dressed up like the Ripper,

1800
01:35:06,233 --> 01:35:09,031
killed your mom, and Paterson,
and four of his birth-mates

1801
01:35:09,103 --> 01:35:10,730
before we finally
stopped him.

1802
01:35:10,805 --> 01:35:11,965
One of the Riverton Seven?

1803
01:35:12,039 --> 01:35:14,439
The one of the seven
with the bad soul.

1804
01:35:15,109 --> 01:35:16,906
The Ripper's soul.
BUG: Jerome?

1805
01:35:17,611 --> 01:35:20,273
Great twist, huh?
Everybody will think you were the killer

1806
01:35:20,347 --> 01:35:23,783
but it turns out the attack came
from a totally unexpected direction.

1807
01:35:23,984 --> 01:35:25,508
You'd lay all this
on Jerome?

1808
01:35:25,586 --> 01:35:27,679
He won't mind.
He's dead.

1809
01:35:27,755 --> 01:35:29,746
You and me will be
Main-Street heroes

1810
01:35:29,824 --> 01:35:31,985
helping each other
forge a new beginning.

1811
01:35:32,059 --> 01:35:34,425
Recovering from
our tragic losses.

1812
01:35:34,495 --> 01:35:37,362
Friends to the end.
What do you say?

1813
01:35:37,531 --> 01:35:38,691
Deal?

1814
01:35:39,734 --> 01:35:41,361
You're pathetic.

1815
01:35:42,169 --> 01:35:44,034
I don't even think
you're Alex.

1816
01:35:45,973 --> 01:35:47,372
I don't know who you are.

1817
01:35:51,212 --> 01:35:54,648
I'm the one that's going to
kill you if you don't say yes.

1818
01:35:54,715 --> 01:35:55,943
And then I'll say
you did it.

1819
01:35:56,350 --> 01:35:58,818
And I'll be the hero
all by myself.

1820
01:35:58,886 --> 01:36:00,751
Leah saw the whole fight.
She'll vouch for me.

1821
01:36:00,821 --> 01:36:02,118
Leah doesn't live
through the night.

1822
01:36:02,189 --> 01:36:03,486
That's part of
the deal, too.

1823
01:36:05,059 --> 01:36:06,788
Whoever or
whatever you are,

1824
01:36:06,861 --> 01:36:09,989
get out of Alex. And go back to hell,
where you came from.

1825
01:36:10,364 --> 01:36:11,729
I mean it.

1826
01:36:13,667 --> 01:36:14,827
Okay.

1827
01:36:16,070 --> 01:36:17,435
But I'll take you with me.

1828
01:36:18,005 --> 01:36:19,267
(GASPING)

1829
01:36:23,410 --> 01:36:25,207
I thought that guy
would never leave.

1830
01:36:26,981 --> 01:36:28,175
Alex.

1831
01:36:31,719 --> 01:36:33,619
Where is the biggest
knife in the kitchen?

1832
01:36:33,788 --> 01:36:34,914
Where it needs to be.

1833
01:36:41,629 --> 01:36:42,687
Condor?

1834
01:36:42,997 --> 01:36:44,157
Crow.

1835
01:36:47,434 --> 01:36:49,163
(GRUNTING IN PAIN)

1836
01:36:53,741 --> 01:36:56,733
It's all right, Bug.
Feels great.

1837
01:36:58,212 --> 01:37:00,009
Feels fucking great.

1838
01:37:02,449 --> 01:37:03,973
Fucking great.

1839
01:37:04,685 --> 01:37:06,550
(SIRENS APPROACHING)

1840
01:37:13,394 --> 01:37:14,520
Fly now.

1841
01:37:21,135 --> 01:37:23,103
I know you're up there.

1842
01:37:24,905 --> 01:37:26,998
And I know we're down here.

1843
01:37:28,943 --> 01:37:29,967
COP 1: Police!

1844
01:37:30,044 --> 01:37:31,636
COP 2: Police!
Open the door!

1845
01:37:31,745 --> 01:37:33,713
Open up!
Open the door!

1846
01:37:34,849 --> 01:37:36,510
Open the door now!

1847
01:37:36,984 --> 01:37:38,576
BUG: I am the condor.

1848
01:37:39,687 --> 01:37:41,655
The Keeper of the Souls.

1849
01:37:43,123 --> 01:37:45,887
I eat death for breakfast.

1850
01:37:45,960 --> 01:37:48,622
I live in a house of blood

1851
01:37:48,696 --> 01:37:50,357
and I accept that.

1852
01:37:50,931 --> 01:37:52,193
COP 3: Break it down!

1853
01:37:52,266 --> 01:37:53,665
BUG: That's all a man can do.

1854
01:37:57,171 --> 01:37:59,230
I was ready to be
arrested that night.

1855
01:37:59,306 --> 01:38:01,137
I wasn't ready for
what happened instead.

1856
01:38:01,208 --> 01:38:02,266
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

1857
01:38:02,343 --> 01:38:03,503
Leah had told
them everything,

1858
01:38:03,577 --> 01:38:05,135
and I was celebrated
as a hero.

1859
01:38:05,212 --> 01:38:06,804
Don't worry about it, man.
They're on your side.

1860
01:38:06,881 --> 01:38:08,610
BUG: Alex Dunkelman
killed his stepfather,

1861
01:38:08,682 --> 01:38:11,048
a cop,
a mother and five of the Riverton Seven.

1862
01:38:11,118 --> 01:38:12,142
Your sister's
right over there.

1863
01:38:12,219 --> 01:38:15,086
BUG: And I alone had stopped him from killing more.

1864
01:38:15,155 --> 01:38:17,589
I didn't feel like
a hero at all.

1865
01:38:18,893 --> 01:38:21,828
But if it makes Riverton
feel safe at night,

1866
01:38:22,329 --> 01:38:24,729
I'll fake that I'm their hero.

1867
01:38:24,798 --> 01:38:26,663
And I'll fake it good.

1868
01:38:27,401 --> 01:38:29,926
Alex wouldn't have it
any other way.

1869
01:38:30,304 --> 01:38:32,636
(ALL CHATTERING)
